### homework
week 7
day 4

### prompt
Write a function called average_array that takes a nonempty array of integers as
an argument and returns their average (aka the mean).

### solution
function average_array(array) {
  var sum = 0;
  for (var i = 0; i < array.length; i++) {
    sum += array[i];
  }
  return sum / array.length;
}

### test
console.log(average_array([23]));
console.log(average_array({{ x }}));

### hint
Here's code for the average_three function which takes a three integers as an
argument and returns their average:
<pre>
function average_three(x, y, z) {
  return (x + y + z) / 3;
}
</pre>

